net.sourceforge.jnlp.controlpanel

Class CommandLine

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sourceforge.jnlp.controlpanel.CommandLine

  • public class CommandLine
extends java.lang.Object
    Encapsulates a command line interface to the deployment configuration.

    The central method is handle(), which calls one of the various 'handle' methods. The commands listed in OptionsDefinitions.getItwsettingsCommands are supported. For each supported command, a method handleCOMMANDCommand exists. This method actually takes action based on the command. Generally, a printCOMMANDHelp method also exists, and prints out the help message for that specific command. For example, see handleListCommand() and printListHelp().

    Sample usage: 
    
 CommandLine cli = new CommandLine();
 // the string array represents input using the command line
 int retVal = cli.handle(new String[] { "help" });
 if (retVal == CommandLine.SUCCESS) {
    // good!
 } else {
    // bad!
 }

        public int handle()
